        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 3:45PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 345 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Nolan. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Blackwell, Nolan, Hylton, Maryneal, Camp Butman, The Intersection Of
Highway 70 And Ranch Road 53, and Lake Sweetwater.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
